Clever without trying to make things seem more impressive than the idea is by being obtuse or redacting too much information. Like other SCP's from this author, this one seems underappreciated,

I agree with PeppersGhost about using bolds for headings in the test logs. Not only does it make the document easier to read, it is the usual practice in preparing a scientific manuscript (underlining or bold and underlined are also used). I suppose that the Results  section should be split into a brief Materials and Methods  and a Results  section. Not really critical though it would allow saying  Which takes the scientific veracity up to 11 on a 10 point scale. Regardless, if I ever write an SCP, I am most definitely stealing this format.

Great clinical tone, as one would expect from a clinician (author is a CRNP I think).

+1

I just wish the author's account hadn't been deleted.







